      },
      "date": "2015-03-12 09:47:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Code-Review+1\n\nLooks good to me. Stephen Champion pointed out that the default settings do result in CPTs on most NUMA systems, though that code will have issues if the system has nodes with different numbers of CPUs. So I do see value in having an easy way to say \"just use the node boundaries\".\n\nReviewed-by: Olaf Weber <olaf@sgi.com>",
